	   <tr><td colspan=2>Erudites make absolute great Necros. To begin with they have the most starting INT of any other race, The Paineel newbie area is a great place to level up untill you can hunt in Toxx forest, and LVL to about 9. Then you are off to EC then to Nro then to Oasis. Can get to LVL 20 easy, and you are not KoS in any of those zones, unless you go to far to the North in Toxx. You may be KoS to the other Erudites. Also do not forget that Erudites can ware Flayed skin armor. Good stuff at lower levels. In fact my necro is LVL 33 and still use a piece or two myself. <br><br>When I started i was not KoS in Kelethin, FP, Nek, or Felwithe if I remember correctly. You can work faction so you are not KoS in Kaladim also if you kill Orcs in Gfay or Goblins in Butcher block. And for those of you that think that ruins your Nek faction you are SO wrong... It ruins your DE warrior guild faction, so just stay away from there and you are fine throughout the rest of the city I should know I have a DE SK that can not get any worse with indigo brotherhood and guards con indifferent to me. You qeynos faction should be KoS when you start however and most druids wont like you, but if your going to play a necro, you had better accept that not everyone is going to Love you. <br><br>Erudites can also you steelsilk which is good stuff (me like). Just sit in Sro for awhile kill things untill either the AC pops (get some Jboots) or the terrorantula spawns (terrorantula silks for steelsilk armor). Both very helpful stuff.<br><br>If you do not chose a Erudite, pick a Dark elf. There is not much cooler then a DE with a skelly pet and weapon with the same graphic as a staff of writhing, e.g. Chetari Wardstaff. Faction is junk almost everywhere but if you are worried about faciton.... you picked the WRONG class to play.<br><br>-Bludysky LVL 33 Erudite Necro<br><br>Faithfully spreading server evil on E-marr<br><br>&quot;If ignorance is bliss, why aren't more people happy?&