	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually in OOT that is one of the few places i will never use fear...&nbsp;&nbsp;The key here is snare..  I just snare then let it get close to water.. Send pet.. Then i always hit with two dots.. By the time i have ebolt on him i have aggro so i just let him follow me around out in the water..My strategy is.. Darkness then let him get close to water, then send pet.. then hit with bond of death and ebolt...  run way out in water with lich up and sit.. your pet will do the rest... kill about 3 til you have to sit and med this way.  This way no worries of ever getting aggro  til some ass runs around with 6 seafuries on him.. geez just take the death for god sake  lol.. I gave up seafuries for now, for igs but not the ice giants in permafrost.. the ones in everfrost near perma zone...  i guess you could go without a pet, but its very risky..  the front two you have need to target then run out on other side of wall that way they dont have straight path to rip your head off..  of the few experiences i have had when they actually got to me they would hit me very hard stun and hit me again  and i be dead... your lucky to get away from one if they get to you when they resist darkness..  cuz i never had, thus thats why the wall is there for safety..  and another thing  when you hit darkness  type /pet attack during spell cast  so it can get some of the aggro...  never use your rogue pet here  it will die when fear resists... i dunno bout many places post 50 without a pet...  thats just crazy in my eyes lol..  better exp i know but i need good old jabober cuz  well  i just like him.  but before 50 i would solo without a pet often like in dl, the barb in wk to name a few..  ill post more if i think of more  my brain is freezing right now...<br>&nbsp;<br>Sphoenix Darkfever</td></tr>
