	   <a name=101907508592603></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101907508592603><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101907508592603>Info for New Necros</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101907508592603#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=103668><span id=Sage>Ishtarra</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>25 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 17th 4:30 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First and foremost, a well played necro of any race can be very powerful.<br><br>Secondly, setting up you PC helps tremendously.&nbsp;&nbsp;Look in the the manual located in your default eq directory for information on setting up hotkeys.  <br><br>Use the full screen mode by pressing F10 once.  This gives you 4 more hotkey slots.  You can arrange the boxes on the screen and resize them.  <br><br>I use alt + spell_gem_number to cast spells.  Hold down the alt key, then press the correspnding number key to cast spells.<br><br>I use ctrl + letter to do things like sit (ctrl+s) and spellbook (ctrl+b).  There are other combos you can do as well.  Look in the manula for help with these.<br><br>Most people want to know what the best race is for necros.  The best race is the one you have fun playing.  Are you going to be in a group or soloing?  The Iksar necro has arguably the best qualites.  They regen, have infravision, have better inate AC, forage, and they have a great starting location in Kunark.  They do get a 20% exp point penalty and are KOS in lots of Kunark and Old World zones.  Most people spend very little time in the Old World and Cabilis is fine for all your needs in Kunark.  Iksar have less downtime and kill stuff faster.  As a casual player, I hated waiting between fights to get my HP up in my mid-levels.  An iksar has much less downtime...so more action. <br><br>Safe journeys...<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

