	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>I think I've found a pretty good way to set my hotkeys up for easy battles. I am a level 7 necro but the same setup could apply to most everyone I think. They are as follows:<br><br>HOTKEY BANK ##<br><br>1. Siphon Strength (a cheap opener to keep my alteration up but I dont always use it)<br>2. Clinging Darkness (I always open with this one)<br>3. Pet Attack<br>4. Poison Bolt<br>5. Fear (i cast this if my pet is really taking a beating or i'm fighting yellows)<br>6. Lifespike (use this sometimes as a DD spell to get that extra edge or if I need to melee)<br><br>Thats about it. A typical battle consists of me simply pressing these keys in succession, usualyl as fast as possible or sometimes twice if I get a lot of resists which suck. Pretty easy.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
