	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101715665247585><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101715665247585>Importance of Int</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=101715665247585#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=69206><span id= >dimle</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>50 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 26th 10:30 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This will probably get me flamed, but I want to say that in my opinion having a high Int is, up to a point, highly overrated for a necro.&nbsp;&nbsp;Int controls your Max mana, not the rate at which you recover it.  Recovery is based on meditation skill.<br><br>With a higher max, when you first go out to hunt it will maybe let you kill two mobs instead of only one, before medding, maybe even three.  But then you have to med Longer to get back to full.  And the longer you stay out hunting mobs, the less difference it makes, cause the limiting factor is how fast you get it Back, not how much you can hold.<br><br>Think of it like a water pistol.  If mine squirts just as fast as yours does, and yours holds much more water -- well, I may have to reload more often, but I can get you just as wet as you can get me, cause it takes you longer to reload.<br><br>Is high Int better than low int?  Sure.  And you want to have Enough of a max to where you don't go dangerously low in only killing one mob. But the difference between 160 Int and 200 Int, below level 50, is not going to make much difference in your life as a necro.<br><br>My two cents. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
