	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 28th 11:04 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.90]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At lower levels (up to 51 or so...) necros fear kite. <br><br>First the mob is snared, then the pet is sent in, the mob is feared so it runs away (it is at this point totally harmless) and then you dot it. Depending on your level you might run along behind it and whack it but that diminishes with levels as sitting and medding becomes a much more usefull, not to mention safe, way to occupy your time.<br><br>Necros are such efficient soloers becuase we have a pet doing dmg for us, hp for mana spells that allow us to regain mana very fast, fear makes a mob totally impotent so dmg does not have to be healed, and we dont die often because we have a variety of escape spells such as FD.<br><br>At higher levels it is even simpler. Root mob, snare mob, dot mob, root mob, mob dies.<br><br>You can get a couple cooking at once too<br>&nbsp;<br>Broxilius Hythloday<br>Chosen Blood and<br>Heretic of Paineel<br>Necromancer, Tallon Zek</td></tr>
